// Marker for tecs-l/scripts/tecs_discovery_loop.sh — 2026-04-10
// TECS-L infinite discovery-loop daemon: 6-step bash pipeline
// (wall → forge → split → absorb → measure → act → validate → record
//  → pollinate → bridge → publish → report) with PID-file supervision.
//
// Reason for noport:
//   - subprocess-heavy (python3 x 12+ invocations per cycle)
//   - PID-file + SIGTERM trap supervision (bash-specific)
//   - interruptible sleep between cycles
//   - depends on nexus-bridge.py (external)
//
// Replacement path:
//   All python3 stages are already ported as .hexa demos under
//   scripts/tecs_*.hexa. A hexa-native daemon should wrap them
//   via exec() + sleep() and persist state in growth_bus.jsonl.
//   Meanwhile this bash driver stays in tecs-l for continuity.
